Subject: [PATCH] C-9 move diagnostics: NO_REVOKE / VERBOSE / MOVE_KLASS toggles + indy-free microbench

Adds three env-gated diagnostic toggles to VM_StoplessCollect to dissect the
post-move hang, plus the StoplessMoveRootsClosure klass filter:
  STOPLESS_NO_REVOKE=1     move+fix roots but skip the revoke sweep
  STOPLESS_MOVE_VERBOSE=1  log klass external_name of each moved object
  STOPLESS_MOVE_KLASS=<s>  only relocate objects whose klass name contains <s>
Also reports skipped= in the collect line.

These pinned the C-9 real-JVM blocker (see docs / memory):
  - LIMIT=0 (no oop_store) ALL-OK; moved>=1 spins -> the root-fixup STORE into a
    live Zero interpreter frame local corrupts interpreter state (Method*=0x22
    dispatch recursion + SIGPROT spin).
  - VERBOSE shows the blind move grabs SYSTEM objects first (java.lang.Class
    mirrors, Runtime, String[]) whose raw metaspace refs (Klass::_java_mirror)
    the root scan doesn't cover -> identity split.
  - The mover is root-only (no tracing): among app objects only interpreter
    stack locals are reachable; array elements and static fields are not
    (STATIC/ARRAY probes move=0).

Test harnesses (invokedynamic-free, System.err phase markers):
  tests/integration/StoplessBench.java, StaticRootGC.java
  tests/integration/ConcatTest.java (isolates the indy "nothing to resolve" bug)
  tests/integration/IntegrityGC.java

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

